; [AI] Z-80 front end stages LD HL,$1400 ($0179 above) as the 6502 entry and
; [AI] pokes the A_VEC/Z_CPU handoff doorbell, so the block runs RELOCATED at
; [AI] $1400-$19FF (file $0400 + $1000); its internal self-references are
; [AI] written as $14xx-$19xx. It is disassembled as real 6502 in
; [AI] FORMAT_6502.s (ca65) and INCBIN'd here byte-for-byte, so each CPU's
; [AI] code is real source in its own assembler (the CPM_RPC6502 / CPM56_6502
; [AI] cross-CPU INCBIN pattern). A 6-and-2 GCR Disk II engine: seek,
; [AI] write/read the D5 AA 96 address field and D5 AA AD data field, and
; [AI] format+verify all 16 sectors of each track. See FORMAT_6502.s for the
; [AI] routine map and data-table layout. Nothing outside the block
; [AI] references an address inside it (the Z-80 hands off via the RPC slot,
; [AI] not a direct address ref), so no cross-CPU EQUs are needed.
; [AI] ===================================================================
